description: Students analyze mechanical principles in depth as they affect human motion. Topics include study of muscular and skeletal systems, skill analysis, and motion measurement techniques. The course includes a laboratory component. Counts toward neuroscience concentration. Offered annually. Prerequisites: BIO 143, BIO 243, and junior
name: Biomechanics
notes: Students in ESTH 374 A must also register for ESTH 374 A lab or B lab.
This course is only open to seniors and juniors.
